Installation
============

Unix
====

Untar the ACE archive in a directory of your choice.
For example:
        cd <ROOT>
        tar -xzf ACE-ilProlog-1.2.20-linux.tar.gz 

Set environment variable ACE_ILP_ROOT to <ROOT>/<ACE>/<OS>
For example:
        export ACE_ILP_ROOT=<ROOT>/ACE-ilProlog-1.2.20-linux/linux

Go to the directory that contains your application.
For example:
        cd <APPLICATION>
        ${ACE_ILP_ROOT}/bin/ace
	
One can also define an alias (to start ACE by typing ACE):
	alias ACE=${ACE_ILP_ROOT}/bin/ace
	

Happy ACE'ing !
